*Is data in your D**NA? Do you like to puzzle, understand processes* *really* *quickly, and* *you are* *proactive and* *decisive**?* *Are you always the one explaining things to other people?* *We are looking for you!*


**About the job**  

We are looking for several data analysts, each with their own area of expertise. The focus area will be Sales & Marketing, Finance and External data. In the role of Global Data Analyst, you will support various stakeholders in the Accell organization. You will develop short and long-term (market) analyses to support and guide the continuous development of our strategy and planning. You continuously optimize and improve your analyses and create high quality dashboards. You collaborate with various teams to refine data strategies and adhere to strict standards for data accuracy and reliability.



As an analyst you are constantly seeking for actionable insights and trends, which leads to sustainable dashboards. You will create data-driven insights, maintain dynamic dashboards and reports, and identify trends to make informed decisions.


**The Department** The function is embedded in the Group Finance department. The Group Data & Advanced Analytics team is a global team who are working cross functional. The Group Data & Advanced Analytics consists of 3 data engineers and 6 data analysts focusing on specific domains. The focus of this role is mainly Sales & Marketing related topics. Together with the data engineers you are constantly working on getting standardized data, where input and validation from your side is needed.



Your location will be one of the Accell offices in Heerenveen. You will have the flexibility to work from home but appreciate being able to come to our office at least twice a week. In addition, you are willing to travel to other locations from time to time.



Your responsibilities


* Create and maintain new dashboards, reports, visualizations and datasets. You take care of one version of the truth in the datasets;
* Monitoring and analyzing trends and developments in the company on one hand and in the market on the other hand, translation of this into concrete actions and chances;
* Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand the business needs and translate this to data driven insights. Herewith you are in close cooperation with the data engineering team;
* Identify trends, patterns and anomalies in data providing actionable recommendations to enhance decision making;
* Gatekeeper of the use of standard templates for the reports;
* Some recurring tasks for maintenance and decision making by the management.


**We believe Cycling moves the world forward!**  

Accell Group focuses on developing, producing, and marketing bicycles, parts and accessories in the middle and upper segment of the market. Cycling incredibly popular and the e-bike is rapidly conquering the world. Accell is growing and there is room to develop, so we want to invest even more in our people. Accell is market leader in Europe with well-known brands such as Batavus, KOGA, Sparta, Haibike, Winora, Raleigh, Lapierre, Ghost and Van Nicholas. XLC is our brand for bicycle parts and accessories. We believe that people have the power to change the world. We keep pushing ourselves to create high-quality, high performance, cutting-edge products driven by the continuous exchange of knowhow and craftmanship.

**What do you bring?**  

You are an analyst who is asking questions. You are innovative and you are passioned for data. You do feel highly responsible and you are able to cope with pressure. It is important that you can bring your vision and plans to stakeholders and the engineers. You are an enthusiastic and convincing person. You are in contact with stakeholders on different levels in the organization. Your enthusiastic attitude is giving a boost to other people.

* Bachelor or Master degree Data Science, Statistics, Business Information Technology, Business Administration or related field;
* 2-5 years of working experience in a comparable function;
* Proficiency in data analysis tools and programming languages (Power BI, SAP Business Objects, Python, SQL). Microsoft Azure is a pré;
* Strong analytical and critical thinking skills;
* Principals as data warehousing, ETL and data models is common language for you;
* You are proactive, analytic, pragmatic and decisive you feel responsible for your tasks;
* Continuous learning mindset to stay updated on data analytics techniques and tools.

 **What we offer**

* The possibility to work partly remote;
* A good salary appropriate to your knowledge and experience;
* 28 vacation days based on fulltime employment;
* Travel allowance;
* Pleasant and informal working atmosphere;
* Plenty of individual learning and development opportunities;
* Home working allowance and flexible workhours;
* Attractive staff discount on bikes and bikes accessories and bike lease arrangement.

**Apply**  

Are you excited and do you see yourself at Accell? Then apply via the button below. For questions about the procedure, please contact our Recruiter Willemijn Meewis at w.meewis@accell.nl.



* Function category: Data
* Education: HBO/WO
* Amount of hours: TBD
